          <!-- TODO: Update the heading with the title of your website -->
          <h1>
            Educational and Advocative Resources
          </h1>
        </div>

        <div class="intro-text">
          Here are sites and articles with information surrounding the topic of mental health and illness,
          including both general and more specific (such as facts or statistics) information.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <br>
    
  
    <h2>
      Educational Resources
    </h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
      <h3>
      <a href="https://www.apa.org/">American Psychological Association (APA)</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          The American Psychological Association provides news, information and research, and advocacy surrounding psychology and mental health.
        </h4>
      </li>
      <li>
      <h3>
        <a href="https://www.nami.org/home">National Association on Mental Illness (NAMI)</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          NAMI is a grassroots mental health organization dedicated to providing support and resources for those affected by mental illness.
        </h4>
      </li>
      <li>
      <h3>
      <a href="https://www.mhanational.org/about">Mental Health America</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          Mental Health America is a non-profit dedicated to supporting and promoting mental health and addressing the needs of those affected by mental
          illness. It mostly provides resources for getting help and ways to help the mental health community.
        </h4>
      </li>
      <li>
      <h3>
      <a href="https://www.nimh.nih.gov/index.shtml">National Institute of Mental Health</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          NIMH is a federal agency for research on mental disorders. It provides resources, news, information on disorders, and reseasrch highlights. It also
          provides funding opportunities.
        </h4>
      </li>
      <li>
      <h3>
        <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us">Psychology Today</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          The Psychology Today site provides articles surrounding various topics in psychology, as well as providing
          mental health resources. It also publishes its own magazines.
        </h4>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <br>
    <br>
    
    <div class="advocacy-img">
    </div>
    <h2>
      Advocacy Groups and Resources
    </h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <h3>
      <a href="https://www.mhanational.org/issues/advocacy-network">Mental Health America’s Advocacy Network</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          Mental Health America's Advocacy Network focuses on legislative advocacy, having implemented policies such as the Affordable Care Act. It provides
          many ways to get involved, including action alerts; various ways to give, such as donating or social media fundraising; and volunteering, among others.
        </h4>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>
      <a href="https://www.nami.org/Get-Involved/What-Can-I-Do/Become-a-Leader-in-the-Mental-Health-Movement">National Alliance on Mental Illness (NAMI)’s “Get Involved” Page</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          NAMI's "Get Involved" provides various specific ways to act, including supporting NAMI, getting involved in one's community, and working with authoriities and companies.
        </h4>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>
      <a href="https://psychcentral.com/blog/what-it-means-to-be-a-mental-health-advocate-and-how-to-become-one/"> Psych Central’s Article on Being a Mental Health Advocate</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          Psych Central's "How to Be an Advocate" article provides a sense of what being an advocate can mean, their role and reason in the community, what advocacy can
          look like, and, of course, how to be one.
        </h4>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>
      <a href="https://www.bevocalspeakup.com/how-to-be-vocal-for-your-community.html">Be Vocal’s Website</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          <em>Be Vocal</em> is a site focusing on speaking up and raising awareness and support. It includes pages such as tips for speaking up for
          oneself and one's community, 
        </h4>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>
      <a href="https://www.apa.org/advocacy/health/">American Psychological Association's Advocacy Page</a>
        </h3>
        <h4>
          The APA's advocacy page emphasizes physical and mental health and focuses legislative actions and policies for easier
          and equal healthcare. They provide several resources and news updates on legislative and other advocacy related events.
        </h4>
      </li>
    </ul>
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
